actuarial hazard function

act.haz <- function(data, time, event, class){
  data <- as.data.frame(data)
  time <- data[,time]
  event <- data[,event]
  class <- data[,class]
  temp_sdf <- survdiff(Surv(time, event) ~ class)
  HR <- (temp_sdf$obs[2]/temp_sdf$exp[2])/(temp_sdf$obs[1]/temp_sdf$exp[1])
  return(HR)
}

gmm2 threshold all data model

gmm_alldata_pfs_fit <- densityMclust(commpass_pfs_all_cox$linear.predictors, G=2, modelNames="E", verbose=F)
commpass_pfs_rset_data$cl_gmm2 <- gmm_alldata_pfs_fit$classification
gmm2_means <- data.frame(means=gmm_alldata_pfs_fit$parameters$mean)
commpass_pfs_rset_data$gmm2_class <- ifelse(gmm_alldata_pfs_fit$classification==2, "high", "low")
commpass_pfs_rset_data$gmm2_class <- factor(commpass_pfs_rset_data$gmm2_class, levels=c("low", "high"))
## actuarial HR
gmm2_thr_HR <- act.haz(commpass_pfs_rset_data, "ttcpfs", "censpfs", "gmm2_class")
